"I think, Watson," he remarked at last, "that of all our cases we have had none more fantastic than
this."

"Save, perhaps, the Sign of Four."

"Well, yes. Save, perhaps, that. And yet this John Openshaw seems to me to be walking amid even
greater perils than did the Sholtos."

"But have you," I asked, "formed any definite conception as to what these perils are?"